DOMPoint.summary: A DOMPoint object represents a 2D or 3D point in a coordinate system; it includes values for the coordinates in up to three dimensions, as well as an optional perspective value.
DOMPoint.title: DOMPoint

DOMPoint.summary: The DOMPointReadOnly interface specifies the coordinate and perspective fields used by DOMPoint to define a 2D or 3D point in a coordinate system.
DOMPoint.title: DOMPointReadOnly

DOMQuad.summary: A DOMQuad is a collection of four DOMPoints defining the corners of an arbitrary quadrilateral. Returning DOMQuads lets getBoxQuads() return accurate information even when arbitrary 2D or 3D transforms are present. It has a handy bounds attribute returning a DOMRectReadOnly for those cases where you just want an axis-aligned bounding rectangle.
DOMQuad.title: DOMQuad

dom-dommatrix.summary: The DOMMatrix interface represents 4x4 matrices, suitable for 2D and 3D operations.
dom-dommatrix.title: DOMMatrix

dom-dommatrixreadonly-dommatrixreadonly.summary: The DOMMatrix constructor creates a new DOMMatrix object which represents 4x4 matrices, suitable for 2D and 3D operations..
dom-dommatrixreadonly-dommatrixreadonly.title: DOMMatrix()

dom-dommatrixreadonly-dommatrixreadonly.summary: The DOMMatrixReadOnly constructor creates a new DOMMatrixReadOnly object which represents 4x4 matrices, suitable for 2D and 3D operations.
dom-dommatrixreadonly-dommatrixreadonly.title: DOMMatrixReadOnly()

dom-dompoint-dompoint.summary: The DOMPoint() constructor creates and returns a new DOMPoint object, given the values for some or all of its properties.
dom-dompoint-dompoint.title: DOMPoint.DOMPoint()

dom-dompointinit-w.summary: The DOMPointInit dictionary's w property is used to specify the w perspective value of a point in space when either creating or serializing to JSON a DOMPoint or DOMPointReadOnly object.
dom-dompointinit-w.title: DOMPointInit.w

dom-dompointinit-x.summary: The DOMPointInit dictionary's x property is used to specify the x component of a point in 2D or 3D space when either creating or serializing a DOMPoint or DOMPointReadOnly.
dom-dompointinit-x.title: DOMPointInit.x

dom-dompointinit-y.summary: The DOMPointInit dictionary's y property is used to specify the y-coordinate of a point in 2D or 3D space when either creating or serializing to JSON a DOMPoint or DOMPointReadOnly object.
dom-dompointinit-y.title: DOMPointInit.y

dom-dompointinit-z.summary: The DOMPointInit dictionary's z property is used to specify the z-coordinate of a point in 2D or 3D space when either creating or serializing to JSON a DOMPoint or DOMPointReadOnly object.
dom-dompointinit-z.title: DOMPointInit.z

dom-dompointreadonly-frompoint.summary: The DOMPointInit dictionary is used to provide the values of the coordinates and perspective when creating and JSONifying a DOMPoint or DOMPointReadOnly object.
dom-dompointreadonly-frompoint.title: DOMPointInit

dom-dompointreadonly-frompoint.summary: The static DOMPointReadOnly method fromPoint() creates and returns a new DOMPointReadOnly object given a source point.
dom-dompointreadonly-frompoint.title: DOMPointReadOnly.fromPoint()

dom-dompointreadonly-tojson.summary: The DOMPointReadOnly method toJSON() returns a DOMPointInit object giving the JSON form of the point object.
dom-dompointreadonly-tojson.title: DOMPointReadOnly.toJSON()

dom-dompointreadonly-w.summary: The DOMPointReadOnly interface's w property holds the point's perspective value, w, for a read-only point in space.
dom-dompointreadonly-w.title: DOMPointReadOnly.w

dom-dompointreadonly-x.summary: The DOMPointReadOnly interface's x property holds the horizontal coordinate, x, for a read-only point in space. This property cannot be changed by JavaScript code in this read-only version of the DOMPoint object.
dom-dompointreadonly-x.title: DOMPointReadOnly.x

dom-dompointreadonly-y.summary: The DOMPointReadOnly interface's y property holds the vertical coordinate, y, for a read-only point in space.
dom-dompointreadonly-y.title: DOMPointReadOnly.y

dom-dompointreadonly-z.summary: The DOMPointReadOnly interface's z property holds the depth coordinate, z, for a read-only point in space.
dom-dompointreadonly-z.title: DOMPointReadOnly.z

dom-domrect-fromrect.summary: The fromRect() property of the DOMRectReadOnly interface creates a new DOMRectReadOnly object with a given location and dimensions.
dom-domrect-fromrect.title: DOMRectReadOnly.fromRect()

dom-domrectreadonly.summary: The DOMRectReadOnly interface specifies the standard properties used by DOMRect to define a rectangle.
dom-domrectreadonly.title: DOMRectReadOnly

dom-domrectreadonly-bottom.summary: The bottom read-only property of the DOMRectReadOnly interface returns the bottom coordinate value of the DOMRect. (Has the same value as y + height, or y if height is negative.)
dom-domrectreadonly-bottom.title: DOMRectReadOnly.bottom

dom-domrectreadonly-domrectreadonlyx-y-w.summary: The DOMRect() constructor creates a new DOMRect object.
dom-domrectreadonly-domrectreadonlyx-y-w.title: DOMRect.DOMRect()

dom-domrectreadonly-height.summary: The height read-only property of the DOMRectReadOnly interface represents the height of the DOMRect.
dom-domrectreadonly-height.title: DOMRectReadOnly.height

dom-domrectreadonly-left.summary: The left read-only property of the DOMRectReadOnly interface returns the left coordinate value of the DOMRect. (Has the same value as x, or x + width if width is negative.)
dom-domrectreadonly-left.title: DOMRectReadOnly.left

dom-domrectreadonly-right.summary: The right read-only property of the DOMRectReadOnly interface returns the right coordinate value of the DOMRect. (Has the same value as x + width, or x if width is negative.)
dom-domrectreadonly-right.title: DOMRectReadOnly.right

dom-domrectreadonly-top.summary: The top read-only property of the DOMRectReadOnly interface returns the top coordinate value of the DOMRect. (Has the same value as y, or y + height if height is negative.)
dom-domrectreadonly-top.title: DOMRectReadOnly.top

dom-domrectreadonly-width.summary: The width read-only property of the DOMRectReadOnly interface represents the width of the DOMRect.
dom-domrectreadonly-width.title: DOMRectReadOnly.width

dom-domrectreadonly-x.summary: The x read-only property of the DOMRectReadOnly interface represents the x coordinate of the DOMRect's origin.
dom-domrectreadonly-x.title: DOMRectReadOnly.x

dom-domrectreadonly-y.summary: The y read-only property of the DOMRectReadOnly interface represents the y coordinate of the DOMRect's origin.
dom-domrectreadonly-y.title: DOMRectReadOnly.y

dommatrixreadonly.summary: The DOMMatrixReadOnly interface represents a 4x4 matrix, suitable for 2D and 3D operations. If this interface defines only read-only matrices, the DOMMatrix interface which inherits from it, add all the properties and the methods to allow to have modifiable matrices.
dommatrixreadonly.title: DOMMatrixReadOnly

dompointreadonly.summary: The DOMPointReadOnly() constructor returns a new DOMPointReadOnly object representing a point in 2D or 3D space, optionally with perspective, whose values cannot be altered by script code.
dompointreadonly.title: DOMPointReadOnly()
